On Receiving Server Certificate:
    Validate digital signature against trusted CA
    Check certificate revocation list (CRL)
    Verify certificate hostname matches server address

If certificate invalid or revoked:
    Terminate connection
    Alert user of potential MITM attack
Else:
    Continue TLS handshake

During Communication:
    Use forward secrecy keys (Ephemeral Diffie-Hellman)
    Verify each message using HMAC and sequence numbers
